olive oil
1 packet Button Mushrooms
2 clove Garlic
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet Gnocchi
1 sachet Herb & Mushroom Seasoning
1 packet cream
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
¼ cup water
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Baby Leaves
½ packet balsamic glaze

• Thinly slice button mushrooms.
• Finely chop garlic.
• Roughly chop roasted almonds.

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of
olive oil over medium-high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook gnocchi, tossing
occasionally, until golden, 6-8 minutes. Transfer
to a bowl.

TIP: Add extra oil if the gnocchi sticks to the pan.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat, with
a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook mushrooms until browned and softened,
8-10 minutes.

• Reduce heat to medium, then add garlic and
herb & mushroom seasoning and cook until
fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Return gnocchi to pan, then add cream,
vegetable stock powder and the water.
• Add half the grated Parmesan cheese and stir
to combine. Simmer until slightly reduced,
3-4 minutes. Season with pepper.

• Meanwhile, in a medium bowl combine baby
leaves, balsamic glaze (see ingredients) and a
drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide creamy mushroom gnocchi between
bowls. Top with balsamic baby spinach.
• Sprinkle with chopped roasted almonds and
remaining parmesan to serve. Enjoy!